===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-much.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ʌtʃ|-ʌtʃ]]
===Etymology===
Middle English, compare Old English ''[[mycel]]''

<!-- determiner, adjective, pronoun, noun... very fuzzy p.o.s. -->

===Adjective===
'''much''' ({{compar}} '''[[more]]''', {{superl}} '''[[most]]''')

# A large amount of.
#: ''I don't have much money.''

====Usage notes====
*'''Much''' is used with [[uncountable]] nouns. The equivalent used with [[countable]] nouns is '''[[many]]'''.

====Synonyms====
*{{informal}} a [[great deal]] of, {{informal}} [[a lot]] of

====Antonyms====
*[[little]]

